      "side": 1,
      "message": "This feels like quite an awkward API.\nHow about passing in an (optional) function that determines the output filename for a given instance? That\u0027s more general and doesn\u0027t have the awkward edge case of applying to only a single instance in the slice.\n\n\n```\n// When filenameForInstance is non-nil, it\u0027s used to generate the\n// Go filename to be written for an instance. If nil, [DefaultFilenameForInstance]\n// will be used. If filenameForInstance returns \"-\" the content will\n// be written to [os.Stdout].\nfunc Generate(ctx *cue.Context, filenameForInstance func(*build.Instance) string, insts ...*build.Instance) error\n```\n\nAlternatively, pass in a function that\u0027s responsible for actually writing the file:\n\n```\nwriteFileForInstance(inst *build.Instance, data []byte) error\n```\n\nThat way we don\u0027t need this code to know about the \"-\" convention.",
